<% layout('layouts/boilerplate') -%>
<section class="legal-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <h1>Cookies Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %></p>
      <p class="lead">This Cookies Policy explains how we use cookies and similar technologies to provide, protect, and improve our services.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="legal-content">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="legal-nav">
      <h4>Legal Documents</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="/terms-of-service">Terms of Service</a></li>
        <li><a href="/cookies-policy" class="active">Cookies Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="/accessibility">Accessibility</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <article>
      <h2>1. What are Cookies</h2>
      <p>Cookies are small text files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit our website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently and to provide information to website owners.</p>

      <h3>How Cookies Work</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Cookies contain information that is transferred to your device's hard drive</li>
        <li>They help us recognize your device when you return to our website</li>
        <li>Cookies can store user preferences and login information</li>
        <li>They enable us to understand how you use our website</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
      
      <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
      <p>These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly and cannot be disabled:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Session Cookies:</strong> Keep you logged in during your visit</li>
        <li><strong>Security Cookies:</strong> CSRF tokens and other security measures</li>
        <li><strong>Load Balancing:</strong> Ensure optimal website performance</li>
        <li><strong>Cookie Consent:</strong> Remember your cookie preferences</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Performance and Analytics Cookies</h3>
      <p>These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Website traffic and user behavior analysis</li>
        <li><strong>Performance Monitoring:</strong> Page load times and error tracking</li>
        <li><strong>A/B Testing:</strong> Testing different website features</li>
        <li><strong>Heat Mapping:</strong> Understanding user interaction patterns</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Functional Cookies</h3>
      <p>These cookies enhance your experience by remembering your preferences:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Language Preferences:</strong> Remember your chosen language</li>
        <li><strong>Theme Settings:</strong> Dark mode or light mode preferences</li>
        <li><strong>Form Data:</strong> Remember information you've entered</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Remember accessibility settings</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Marketing and Advertising Cookies</h3>
      <p>These cookies are used to deliver relevant advertising and measure campaign effectiveness:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Retargeting:</strong> Show relevant ads on other websites</li>
        <li><strong>Social Media:</strong> Enable sharing and social media integration</li>
        <li><strong>Email Marketing:</strong> Track email campaign effectiveness</li>
        <li><strong>Conversion Tracking:</strong> Measure advertising performance</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
      <p>We may allow third-party services to set cookies on our website. These services have their own privacy policies:</p>

      <h3>Analytics Services</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><strong>Hotjar:</strong> <a href="https://www.hotjar.com/legal/policies/privacy" target="_blank">Hotjar Privacy Policy</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Social Media</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Facebook:</strong> Social sharing and advertising</li>
        <li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> Professional networking integration</li>
        <li><strong>Twitter/X:</strong> Social media sharing</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Communication Tools</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email Services:</strong> Newsletter and transactional emails</li>
        <li><strong>Customer Support:</strong> Live chat and help desk tools</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Cookie Duration</h2>
      <p>Cookies can be classified by how long they remain on your device:</p>

      <h3>Session Cookies</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Temporary cookies that are deleted when you close your browser</li>
        <li>Used for essential website functionality</li>
        <li>Help maintain your session while browsing</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Persistent Cookies</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Remain on your device for a set period or until manually deleted</li>
        <li>Used to remember your preferences between visits</li>
        <li>Enable personalized experiences</li>
        <li>Typical duration: 30 days to 2 years</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h2>
      
      <h3>Browser Settings</h3>
      <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Block all cookies:</strong> Prevent all cookies from being set</li>
        <li><strong>Block third-party cookies:</strong> Allow only first-party cookies</li>
        <li><strong>Delete existing cookies:</strong> Remove cookies already stored</li>
        <li><strong>Notification settings:</strong> Get notified when cookies are set</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Browser-Specific Instructions</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Settings > Privacy and Security > Cookies and other site data</li>
        <li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Settings > Privacy & Security > Cookies and Site Data</li>
        <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences > Privacy > Manage Website Data</li>
        <li><strong>Edge:</strong> Settings > Cookies and site permissions > Cookies and site data</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Opt-Out Tools</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank">Google Analytics Opt-out</a></li>
        <li><strong>Ad Choices:</strong> <a href="http://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank">Digital Advertising Alliance</a></li>
        <li><strong>Network Advertising:</strong> <a href="http://www.networkadvertising.org/choices/" target="_blank">NAI Opt-out</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Impact of Disabling Cookies</h2>
      <p>Disabling certain cookies may affect your experience on our website:</p>

      <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Cannot be disabled without affecting core functionality</li>
        <li>May prevent you from logging in or accessing secure areas</li>
        <li>Could cause website features to not work properly</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Non-Essential Cookies</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Safe to disable without breaking website functionality</li>
        <li>May result in less personalized experience</li>
        <li>Could affect our ability to improve the website</li>
        <li>May see less relevant advertising</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Mobile Devices and Apps</h2>
      <p>Our mobile applications may use similar technologies:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Device Identifiers:</strong> Unique identifiers for analytics and personalization</li>
        <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> Storing preferences and app data locally</li>
        <li><strong>Push Notifications:</strong> Sending relevant updates and information</li>
        <li><strong>Location Services:</strong> Providing location-based features (with permission)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. Data Protection and Security</h2>
      <p>We take the security of cookie data seriously:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Cookies are transmitted securely using HTTPS encryption</li>
        <li>Sensitive information is never stored in cookies</li>
        <li>We regularly review and update our cookie practices</li>
        <li>Third-party services are carefully vetted for security and privacy compliance</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Updates to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Cookies Policy from time to time to reflect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Changes in cookie technology</li>
        <li>New features or services on our website</li>
        <li>Changes in legal requirements</li>
        <li>Updates to third-party services we use</li>
      </ul>

      <p>When we make significant changes, we will notify you by updating the "Last updated" date and may provide additional notice through our website or email.</p>

      <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about our use of cookies or this policy, please contact us:</p>
      
      <div class="contact-info">
        <h4>Cookie Policy Contact Information</h4>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:<%= process.env.ADMIN_EMAIL || 'privacy@asparsh.com' %>"><%= process.env.ADMIN_EMAIL || 'privacy@asparsh.com' %></a></p>
        <p><strong>Subject Line:</strong> "Cookie Policy Inquiry"</p>
        <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> We typically respond within 1-2 business days</p>
      </div>

      <div class="last-updated">
        <p>This cookies policy was last updated on <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %>. Previous versions are available upon request.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
